    "name": "OmniCharge - Operator Plan Management",
    "description": "StartFragment\n\n# OmniCharge – Operator Plan Management\n\nThis collection contains APIs for managing **Operators** and their associated **Recharge Plans** in the OmniCharge microservices system.\n\nIt allows users to:\n\n- Register telecom operators (e.g., Jio, Airtel)\n    \n- Manage operator details (view, update, delete)\n    \n- Create and manage recharge plans linked to operators\n    \n\n---\n\n## 📌 Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://localhost:8086/aperatormanagement\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n## 📂 Collection Structure\n\n### 🔹 Operator APIs\n\n- Create Operator\n    \n- Get All Operators\n    \n- Get Operator by ID\n    \n- Update Operator\n    \n- Delete Operator\n    \n\n### 🔹 Plan APIs\n\n- Create Plan\n    \n- Get All Plans\n    \n- Get Plan by ID\n    \n- Update Plan\n    \n- Delete Plan\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Recommended Execution Flow\n\n1. Create Operator\n    \n2. Fetch Operators\n    \n3. Update Operator (if needed)\n    \n4. Create Plan (linked to operator)\n    \n5. Fetch Plans\n    \n6. Update Plan\n    \n7. Delete Plan\n    \n8. Delete Operator\n    \n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ Important Notes\n\n- A **Plan must always be linked to an existing Operator**\n    \n- Use valid `operatorId` while creating or updating plans\n    \n- Delete **Plans before Operators** to avoid dependency issues\n    \n- API responses do not include IDs (handled internally in database)\n    \n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ Environment Setup (Recommended)\n\nCreate a Postman Environment variable:\n\n```\nbase_url = http://localhost:8086/aperatormanagement\n\n ```\n\nThen use:\n\n```\n{{base_url}}/operators/register\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Status Codes\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| 200 | Request successful |\n| 204 | Resource deleted successfully |\n| 400 | Bad request / validation error |\n| 500 |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
